# Deployment Workflow

When you complete code changes to the basarim-app project:

1. Run `git add -A`, `git commit -m "<descriptive message>"`, and `git push` from the basarim-app directory.
2. Request `git_write` and `network` permissions if the sandbox blocks these commands.
3. Do this automatically—do not ask the user to run these commands themselves.

Exception: Skip if the user explicitly says they will deploy manually or prefers not to push.
